  "body": "The idea is to improve readability of the text based debugger by clearing previous output before printing the next step. That way, changes appear (mostly) in place and your eyes don't need to move in order to stay current. Additionally, it removes the clutter of outdated steps that were skipped over. Ideally there would be a new shortcut to 'scroll' up/down through a timeline of steps.\r\n\r\nJust a simple/easy interim solution before a more robust solution is implemented via ncurses or integration into a visual debugger.",
